<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99261048939280></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99261048939280><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99261048939280>Low level soloing.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=99261048939280#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 15th 9:08 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp; Wizards are quite possibly the most difficult class to solo at lower levels. I have a level 21 wizard now and I did much up my leveling up from level 16 in Lake of Ill Omen and in Timorous Deep. I can usually only go on EQ early in the morning EST and there rarely were enough people to make a group. I did, however, find a way to solo at those places and I leveled up fairly quickly. <br>    Since you cannot bind anywhere in Timorous Deep, I suggest you bind on the dock in the Oasis of Marr that way if you get into too much trouble you can gate back there. Go to the first ogre camp where people usually camp The Great Oowomp. Yellow ogres are possibly to kill, but I suggest waiting before you kill those. Go ahead and do the usual root nuke root nuke order, but make sure you have both shielding and shieldskin on. Also have shadow step and gate memorized. This process is rather tedious without breeze or clarity, but it's worth it. Although Timorous is a great place, I don't suggest it 'til level 18. At levels 16 and 17, Lake of Ill Omen would probably be better because there most likely are a lot of people near the mill for a last minute yelling for help thing. The thing that I liked about Ill Omen so much is the fact that Sabretooth __Tigers__, which should con yellow to you, are easily rooted and nuked. You'll probably end up medding after every kill, but you'll have gotten enough exp to make up for it. Plus they drop sabretooth fangs which go for 1 pp at vendors.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
